			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: High Agro songs?<a name="52834"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 20 04 1:47 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In my experience, all you can do is twist dots, and hope no big heals go off, and - god forbid, have the freaking chanter slow the kite mob.  You can keep agro if you have it first, but stripping it will be very difficult, if not downright impossible.
<br />

<br />
Basically, I do the same thing I do when I'm pulling normally.  When the mob in camp gets to 50%, I run out and grab another mob.  I get back to camp at between 30-5% on the original mob w/ my pull and chant kite it until the first mob goes down.  The difference in this case, though, is that you just have to kite it the duration of the other mob going down.
<br />

<br />
I've been doing this in PoV outer/inner a lot lately.  I've been in *gasp* pickup groups there (shoot me, please?) with no CC.  Most chanters who go there when I'm there are 58-59, and cannot mez the mobs. At 61, I cannot either.  
<br />

<br />
The outer/inner camp is a fast camp if you can always have the next mob outside, ready for when the current mob goes down.  The problem, though, is that when you almost clear both camps, and you pull from way back, you may get a pop on the pull.  Insta add.  It's really not a problem, though, even w/ no CC.  Just have the MT tag one, have the rest of the group assist the MT, and then twist 4 dots on the other mob, kiting it away from the healer.  
<br />

<br />
The ramifications of this are numerous, though.  First off, it means you just can't have enough song spots to really be useful to the group in the standard bard ways.  When I'm in alternate CC mode, I have selos, 4 or 5 dots, SSoQ, Largo's, and one free slot (or the 5th dot).  When we have only one mob in the camp, I'll melee and twist dots, swapping a drum just for the instance the dot songs go off, so my dps goes up, but I'm not overhasting, str/dex/agi, atk buffing the group.  Basically, I'm not being a bard in the mold.  
<br />

<br />
Secondly, some people just will not understand what's happening, not matter how well you describe it to them.  That's pickup groups, though, I guess.  The druids will try to snare and root it, w/o telling you, so while you're kiting it around, you run right into it, lol.  Rangers will do that and then go over to try to tank it a little.  Pally's will throw stuns at it and try to multi tank.  Then they'll complain about being oom after the double pulls.  Clerics will stand right in the center of the kite area, and get agro for each CH, and complain about the bug on them and why they can't heal now.  Slowers will slow the kite mob, and then they have to kite it, because our dots just can't strip agro.
<br />

<br />
Thirdly is the debate between CC methods.  Standard CC w/o a chanter is to kite the mob away, and root it/slow it, or to off tank it (if you have someone to off tank).  For a hardcore XP group w/ a bard, though, this is pointless.  The bard can keep the mob away from the rest of the group using no mana.  Less mana spent = less down time.  Some people are too uptight, though, and this is the only way for them to feel safe (heh, even though root can break any tick).
<br />

<br />
If someone else gets agro, though, you have to adjust.  If a caster gets agro, run up to them and pulse selos, to help them kite, and keep twisting dots.  You likely won't get agro back, but you'll still be doing some dps.  The problem though is that the other kiter now has to concentrate on the kite mob instead of the group, so two of you are out of it now.  If the healer gets agro, everything sucks.  If you can strip agro, you likely will very quickly, otherwise your only option is to get the tank to multi, which means now 2 mobs are beating on your tank, sucking down 2x the mana from the cleric.  Either get the slower to slow (which may mean the slower is going to be kiting now), or root it away to split it.
<br />

<br />
That's been my PoV experience as CC w/o a mez.  To answer your question, though, no, we do not have really any agro songs.</span></td>
