				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: High Agro songs?<a name="54560"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 31 04 2:24 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Over on the sony forums theres talk about what bards want as improvements.  I started a thread around the same time about specifically this issue which has basically split bards down the middle.  Some say its not our role, others (like me) say it should be part of our versatile nature.
<br />

<br />
Reason I posted was basically being sick of seeing chain and leather classes picked to tank in favor of a plate class - that just seems wrong to me.  But the other reasons that various people have raised have all been valid.
<br />

<br />
With the voting thats gone on over there, bard taunt has made the list of items that Tremelo is maintaining.  Where it goes from here is up to the dev's, they are looking at it.  But if it ends up favorably, then hopefully bards will end up with some sort of agro generation.
<br />

<br />
As a side note to this I've noticed lately (as have many others it seems) that DoT agro is far less than what it was.  Meaning our chances of getting delibrate agro having fallen even further.
<br />

<br />
Best suggestion I've seen so far has been to replace the lev 3 song with a +agro song, which could grow with the bard.  Wouldnt be hard to do, just have it add lev + 5 pts, modifiable by singing or percussion, or something like that.  that wouldnt be higher than proper tank classes, and would limit how a bard could utilise the ability - tradeoff damage for the extra agro.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
